{"TopicId":132016,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Jet issues","CreatedByName":"Zighator","CreatedById":158539,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T15:39:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Zighator","CreatedById":158539,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T15:39:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, so i made this plane, i dont know what is wrong with it but it is realy unstable, at take-off it just starts to roll\u002B it strafes right when taking off. Can you please give me any suggestion on what to change as i realy like the design.. thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i65.tinypic.com/behgk3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022behgk3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-13T16:11:54Z\u0022 title=\u002202/13/2016 04:11  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Zighator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T15:56:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA picture would be handy. Chances are though that you haven\u0027t got the wheels perfectly aligned.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Choctofliatrio2.0","CreatedById":154657,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T16:06:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222406996\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132016\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455377961\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158539\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Zighator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, Zighator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, so i made this plane, i dont know what is wrong with it but it is realy unstable, at take-off it just starts to roll\u002B it strafes right when taking off. Can you please give me any suggestion on what to change as i realy like the design.. thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWheels could be the problem. If it rolls once it leaves the runway, check where your Centers of Mass, Lift, and Thrust are.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T16:09:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWheels, or slightly off-center tail\\control surfaces. Sometimes it\u0027s hard to place everything totally symmetrical, when you are going for a certain look \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zighator","CreatedById":158539,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T16:13:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe plane is full of control surfaces so they might be the problem :/\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qromodynmc","CreatedById":87139,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T18:50:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo many wingy thingy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to remind that overcomplicating wings always will hurt your plane.Use procedural wings instead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"I_Killed_Jeb","CreatedById":84817,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T18:54:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nway too much wing... but that\u0027s whatever\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni\u0027d bet that it\u0027s your gears being mounted on your wings causing the wing flex at takeoff to veer you off\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SurrealShock","CreatedById":158548,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T19:02:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-04-25T01:20:05Z\u0022 title=\u002204/25/2024 01:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Apr 25\u0022\u003EApril 25\u003C/time\u003E by SurrealShock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"I_Killed_Jeb","CreatedById":84817,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-13T23:59:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222407353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132016\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455390174\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158548\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SurrealShock\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, SurrealShock said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThe problem is that the CoL is way too far behind the CoM. Move it closer so it is partially inside the CoM. \u003C/strong\u003EYou can do this by changing the position of the wings. One other problem you might be facing is that the gears may be unstable on your craft. I usually just add a crap ton of struts to fix this because I have no real solution for this problem. :/ Make sure that the TWR is above around 1.2 also.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is completely unnecessary and depending on the fuel tank arrangement can cause irrecoverable instability as the CoM shifts backwards.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SurrealShock","CreatedById":158548,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-14T02:15:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-04-25T01:17:57Z\u0022 title=\u002204/25/2024 01:17  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Apr 25\u0022\u003EApril 25\u003C/time\u003E by SurrealShock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"I_Killed_Jeb","CreatedById":84817,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-14T04:15:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222408025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132016\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455416124\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158548\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SurrealShock\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, SurrealShock said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAssuming that the fuel drains evenly throughout the craft according to the wiki:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022line-height:1.5em;list-style-type:disc;margin:.3em 0px 0px 1.6em;padding:0px;color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-bottom:.1em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ECOL ahead of COM \u2192 Flips or turns uncontrollably\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-bottom:.1em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ECOL inside COM \u2192 Excessively maneuverable; needs constant course correction\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-bottom:.1em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ECOL closely behind of COM \u2192 More maneuverable\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-bottom:.1em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ECOL further behind of COM \u2192 More stable\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-bottom:.1em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ECOL very far behind of COM \u2192 Very hard to correct course; likely to flip up or nosedive\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-bottom:.1em;\u0022\u003E\n\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd the craft above has a perfectly fine CoM/CoL distance for all but the most acrobatic usage.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zighator","CreatedById":158539,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-14T16:17:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for all the replies \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E i made another less complicated plane which is stable and easily manuverable at the same time \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}